@startuml Project_Roadmap_Detailed

title Backend Systems Lab — Detailed Project Roadmap\nv1.0 · April – July 2026

!define RECTANGLE class

skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
  BorderColor #AAAAAA
  RoundCorner 12
}

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE (top section)
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

rectangle "System Architecture" as arch #F0F0F0 {

  actor Client

  rectangle "Rate Limiter\n(Token bucket · per IP / endpoint)" as RL #FFE8E0
  rectangle "Load Balancer\n(Round-robin · health checks · failover)" as LB #EDE8FF

  rectangle "Backend Servers" as SERVERS {
    rectangle "Server 1" as S1 #E0F5EE
    rectangle "Server 2" as S2 #E0F5EE
    rectangle "Server 3" as S3 #E0F5EE
  }

  rectangle "Redis Clone\n(Shared cache · rate limit counters · sessions)" as REDIS #E0EEF8

  Client --> RL : HTTP request
  RL --> LB : Allowed request
  LB --> S1 : Route
  LB --> S2 : Route
  LB --> S3 : Route

  S1 --> REDIS : Cache read/write
  S2 --> REDIS : Cache read/write
  S3 --> REDIS : Cache read/write

  REDIS ..> RL : Shared counters (feedback)

  note right of RL
    Checks Redis for current
    request counts before allowing.
    Increments counter on each pass.
    Returns 429 when limit exceeded.
  end note

  note right of LB
    Uses Redis for session
    persistence (sticky routing).
    Reads server health state.
    Supports round-robin & least-conn.
  end note

  note right of REDIS
    Single source of truth for
    rate limit state, session IDs,
    and cached responses.
    RESP wire protocol over TCP.
  end note
}

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' MILESTONES — REDIS CLONE
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

rectangle "Redis Clone" as redis {
    RECTANGLE "M1: Redis core\n(RESP + store)\n(Apr 1 – Apr 14, 2026)\n(Weeks 1-2)" as redis1
    note right of redis1
      - Implement RESP protocol parser & encoder.
      - Build in-memory Store with TTL support.
      - Support SET, GET, INCR, DEL, EXISTS commands.
      - Write unit tests for RESP parsing.
    end note

    RECTANGLE "M2: Redis server\n+ concurrency\n(Apr 15 – Apr 21, 2026)\n(Week 3)" as redis2
    note right of redis2
      - Build asyncio TCP server on port 6380.
      - Handle concurrent client connections.
      - Implement command dispatcher (PING, SET, GET, INCR, DEL, EXISTS).
      - Test with redis-benchmark (100 concurrent clients).
    end note

    RECTANGLE "M3: Advanced commands\n+ tests\n(Apr 22 – Apr 28, 2026)\n(Week 4)" as redis3
    note right of redis3
      - SET ... EX N expiry with lazy eviction.
      - Atomic INCR under concurrent access.
      - ERR for unknown commands, graceful handling of malformed input.
      - >= 10,000 ops/sec benchmark target.
    end note
}

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' MILESTONES — RATE LIMITER
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

rectangle "Rate Limiter" as rate_limiter {
    RECTANGLE "M4: Rate limiter core\n+ Redis integration\n(Apr 29 – May 12, 2026)\n(Weeks 5-6)" as rl1
    note right of rl1
      - Token bucket algorithm via Redis INCR + TTL.
      - Per-IP rate limiting with rl:{ip}:{endpoint} keys.
      - aiohttp middleware server on port 8080.
      - X-RateLimit-Remaining & Retry-After headers.
    end note

    RECTANGLE "M5: Per-endpoint config\n(May 13 – May 19, 2026)\n(Week 7)" as rl2
    note right of rl2
      - Per-endpoint rate limit overrides.
      - No INCR on rejected requests (counter unchanged).
      - Distributed: multiple instances share Redis state.
      - Burst traffic simulation tests.
    end note
}

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' MILESTONES — LOAD BALANCER
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

rectangle "Load Balancer" as load_balancer {
    RECTANGLE "M6: Server pool\n+ round-robin\n(May 20 – Jun 2, 2026)\n(Weeks 8-9)" as lb1
    note right of lb1
      - BackendServer model with health status tracking.
      - Round-robin & least-connections algorithms.
      - Request forwarding to backend servers (8001-8003).
      - Active connection counting.
    end note

    RECTANGLE "M7: Health checker\n+ failover\n(Jun 3 – Jun 9, 2026)\n(Week 10)" as lb2
    note right of lb2
      - Periodic health checks every 5s (configurable).
      - Mark UNHEALTHY after 3 consecutive failures.
      - Re-enter pool after 3 successful checks.
      - Return 503 when all servers unhealthy.
    end note

    RECTANGLE "M8: Session persistence\nvia Redis\n(Jun 10 – Jun 16, 2026)\n(Week 11)" as lb3
    note right of lb3
      - Session cookie pins client to server via Redis.
      - Clear session when pinned server is unhealthy.
      - X-Served-By response header.
      - Graceful drain and recovery support.
    end note
}

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' MILESTONES — INTEGRATION & POLISH
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

rectangle "Integration & Polish" as integration {
    RECTANGLE "M9: Full integration\n+ E2E tests\n(Jun 17 – Jun 30, 2026)\n(Weeks 12-13)" as int1
    note right of int1
      - Full pipeline: Client -> RL -> LB -> Server -> Redis.
      - 150-request burst test (100 OK, 50 rejected 429).
      - Kill server mid-run -> traffic reroutes.
      - Redis holds rate limit counters + session mappings.
    end note

    RECTANGLE "M10: Performance\nbenchmarking\n(Jul 1 – Jul 7, 2026)\n(Week 14)" as int2
    note right of int2
      - 500 concurrent clients, 0% error rate (locust).
      - RL adds <= 2ms latency per request.
      - LB handles >= 1,000 req/s across 3 servers.
      - Recovery from server failure within 15s.
    end note

    RECTANGLE "M11: Docs + polish\n+ v1.0 tag\n(Jul 8 – Jul 14, 2026)\n(Week 15)" as int3
    note right of int3
      - Architecture diagrams (hand-drawn style).
      - README with quickstart & component descriptions.
      - API docs for HTTP endpoints & RESP commands.
      - Tag v1.0.0 release.
    end note
}

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' CONNECTIONS — Critical Path
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

redis1 --> redis2 : "Finish by Apr 14"
redis2 --> redis3 : "Finish by Apr 21"
redis3 --> rl1  : "Redis ready -> Rate Limiter"
redis2 --> lb1  : "Redis server ready"

rl1 --> rl2   : "Finish by May 12"
rl2 --> int1  : "Rate Limiter complete"

lb1 --> lb2   : "Finish by Jun 2"
lb2 --> lb3   : "Finish by Jun 9"
lb3 --> int1  : "Load Balancer complete"

int1 --> int2 : "Finish by Jun 30"
int2 --> int3 : "Finish by Jul 7"

@enduml
